'''Brud Talbot''' (September 16, 1938 – November 20, 1986) was an American film actor, producer, director and writer.

He played George in ''[[Force of Impulse]]'' (1961),<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=d6OTDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA72 |title=Astor Pictures: A Filmography and History of the Reissue King, 1933–1965 |first=Michael R. |last=Pitts |publisher=[[McFarland Publishing]] |date=April 25, 2019 |page=72 |isbn=9781476636283}}</ref> by [[Saul Swimmer]].<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ukFl5C_3npMC&pg=PA130 |title=Force of Impulse |year=1962 |volume=13 |first=Daniel |last=Blum |journal=[[Screen World]] |page=130 |publisher=Biblo & Tannen Publishers |isbn=9780819603036}}</ref> He appeared in ''[[Finger on the Trigger (film)|Finger on the Trigger]]'' (1965) along [[Rory Calhoun]] and [[Todd Martin]].<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VCQ9AErr-uMC&pg=PA114 |title=Finger on the Trigger |journal=[[Screen World]] |first=John A. |last=Willis |author-link=John A. Willis |publisher=Biblo & Tannen Publishers |year=1966 |page=114 |isbn=9780819603074}}</ref>

He was adapting along Ernest Greenberg the autobiography ''Where the Money Was'', by [[Willie Sutton]], into a film, and offered [[Dustin Hoffman]] the role, but he rejected it.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kUhOCLKECyQC&pg=PA123 |title=Dustin Hoffman: Hollywood's Antihero |first=Jeff |last=Lenburg |publisher=[[iUniverse]] |date=May 1, 2001 |page=123 |isbn=9780595182701}}</ref>

